Welcome to SilverStack Guacamole Lab! 🖥️

Apache Guacamole is running internally at http://localhost:__GUAC_PORT__/guacamole
Nginx reverse proxy is listening on port 80 (internal)
MariaDB database is running on port 3306 (internal)
guacd proxy daemon is listening on port 4822 (internal)
XRDP desktop server is listening on port 3389 (internal)

Tools:
- cloudflared         Cloudflare Tunnel for public access
- guacd 1.6.0         Guacamole proxy daemon (compiled from source)
- tomcat10            Apache Tomcat 10 (Jakarta EE)
- mariadb             Production-grade MySQL-compatible database
- xrdp                Remote Desktop Protocol server
- xfce4               Lightweight desktop environment

Default Guacamole credentials:    guacadmin  /  guacadmin
Default RDP credentials:
  Username: __RDP_USER__   Password: (shown in lab-init logs → run: guac-logs-init)

To expose Guacamole publicly via Cloudflare Tunnel:

  1. Go to dash.cloudflare.com/one → Networks → Connectors
  2. Create tunnel → choose Cloudflared → name it (e.g. guacamole-lab) → save
  3. Copy & run the install command shown:  sudo cloudflared service install <token>
  4. Add a published application route:
       Subdomain: desktop   Domain: yourdomain.com
       Service:   HTTP      URL:    localhost:80
  5. Guacamole is now live at https://desktop.yourdomain.com/guacamole

Quick commands:
  guac-status      guac-logs        guac-logs-init   guac-restart
  guacd-logs       xrdp-logs        nginx-logs       nginx-status     nginx-reload
  db-status        db-logs          db-restart       guac-db          guac-connections
